# Ambx — Ruby USB driver and applications for Philips amBX devices

By Etienne van Delden de la Haije, Martijn de Boer, and Gert-Jan de Boer. See AUTHORS for details.

A cross-platform Ruby toolkit for controlling Philips amBX USB devices — lights, fans, and rumble — from macOS and Linux.

Licensed under the BSD license. See LICENSE for details.

---

## Applications

| App | Location | Description |
|-----|----------|-------------|
| **menubar** | `applications/menubar/` | macOS status-bar app (Platypus) with color/fan presets |
| **ambilight** | `applications/ambilight/` | Screen-capture ambient light loop (ruby-vips) |
| **boblight** | `applications/boblight/` | stdin bridge for the Boblight/XBMC protocol |
| **setcolor** | `applications/setcolor/setcolor.rb` | One-shot CLI — set all lights to an RGB color |
| **setfan** | `applications/setcolor/setfan.rb` | One-shot CLI — set fan speed |

---

## Library — libambx

`libambx/` is the canonical USB driver library.
The published gem includes library code only; files in `applications/` are repository-only and excluded from gem packaging.

### Gem install and import

```ruby
# Gemfile
gem "libambx"
```

### Namespace

| Name | Notes |
|------|-------|
| `Ambx::Protocol` | USB IDs, endpoint addresses, opcodes |
| `Ambx::Lights` | Light address constants |
| `Ambx::Fans` | Fan address constants |
| `Ambx::Rumbler` | Keyboard rumbler address constants |
| `Ambx::Error::CannotClaim` | Raised when interface claim fails |
| `Ambx::Packet` | Value object for building USB packets |

### Quick start

```ruby
require "libambx"

Ambx.connect
Ambx.open

# Build a typed packet (preamble + clamping built in):
Ambx.write Ambx::Packet.set_color(Ambx::Lights::WWCENTER, 0, 255, 128)
Ambx.write Ambx::Packet.set_fan(Ambx::Fans::LEFT, 200)

Ambx.close

# Or use raw arrays (backward compatible):
Ambx.write [0xA1, Ambx::Lights::LEFT, 0x03, 255, 0, 0]
```

### Ambx class-method reference

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Ambx.connect` | Scan USB tree for the amBX device; returns `true`/`false` |
| `Ambx.open` | Open and claim the USB interface |
| `Ambx.write(bytes_or_packet)` | Send a 6-byte command to all open handles |
| `Ambx.close(clear_lights = false)` | Release the USB interface; optionally blanks all lights |
| `Ambx.reconnect!(max_attempts: 3, delay: 1.0)` | Retry connect+open, useful in long-running apps |

### Ambx::Packet

```ruby
Ambx::Packet.set_color(light_id, r, g, b)  # => Packet
Ambx::Packet.set_fan(fan_id, speed)         # => Packet
pkt.to_a                                    # => [0xA1, id, 0x03, r, g, b]
pkt.bytes                                   # => same, frozen
```

Float arguments are rounded and clamped to `0..255` automatically.

### Ambx::Lights constants

```
LEFT  = 0x0B    RIGHT = 0x1B
WWLEFT = 0x2B   WWCENTER = 0x3B   WWRIGHT = 0x4B
```

### Ambx::Fans constants

```
LEFT = 0x5B  RIGHT = 0x6B
```

### Ambx::Rumbler constants

```
KEYBOARD = 0x7B
```

### Ambx::Protocol constants

```
USB_VENDOR_ID  = 0x0471    USB_PRODUCT_ID = 0x083F
ENDPOINT_OUT   = 0x02      ENDPOINT_IN    = 0x81
SET_LIGHT_COLOR          = 0x03
SET_TIMED_COLOR_SEQUENCE = 0x72
```

### Additional USB device IDs

`Ambx.connect` supports multiple devices and can match extra amBX-compatible USB IDs via
`AMBX_USB_DEVICE_IDS`:

```bash
AMBX_USB_DEVICE_IDS=1234:abcd,0x5678:0x9abc bundle exec ruby your_app.rb
```

Format: comma-separated `vendor:product` hex pairs (with or without `0x` prefixes).

