## Dependencies

```
Ruby  >= 3.0        (developed and tested on Ruby 4.0)
libusb              system library — brew install libusb
libusb gem          runtime dependency of libambx
ruby-vips           required by repository apps only (not in the gem)
```

Full instructions: INSTALL

---

## Running the CLI tools

```bash
bundle exec ruby applications/setcolor/setcolor.rb 255 0 0   # all lights red
bundle exec ruby applications/setcolor/setfan.rb 128          # fans at 50%
```

---

## Testing

Unit tests run without a physical device. All USB calls are stubbed.

```bash
bundle exec rake            # run all tests (default)
bundle exec rake test       # explicit
```

The suite uses **minitest** with BDD-style `describe`/`it` blocks (`minitest/spec`).

| Test file | What it covers |
|-----------|----------------|
| `test/unit/ambx/packet_test.rb` | Preamble, byte layout, clamping, float rounding, immutability |
| `test/unit/ambx/protocol_test.rb` | All protocol constants, endpoint direction bits, compat alias |
| `test/unit/ambx/lights_test.rb` | All light addresses, 0xB lower-nibble convention, compat alias |
| `test/unit/ambx/driver_test.rb` | write, close, connect, reconnect! with fake USB handles |

---

## Project layout

```
libambx/
  libambx.rb                  entrypoint (require this)
  communication/ambx.rb       Ambx class — connect, open, write, close, reconnect!
  data/protocoldefinitions.rb Ambx::Protocol
  data/lights.rb              Ambx::Lights
  ambx/packet.rb              Ambx::Packet value object

applications/
  menubar/                    macOS Platypus status-bar app
  ambilight/                  screen-capture ambilight loop
  boblight/                   Boblight protocol bridge
  setcolor/                   setcolor.rb + setfan.rb CLIs
  combustd/                   daemon stub (Phase 2)

test/
  test_helper.rb              LIBUSB stub, shared helpers
  unit/ambx/                  unit tests (no hardware required)

examples/
  test-loop/                  quick smoke test — ruby test-loop.rb
```

